- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the economic aspects of Cloud computing, which falls under the scope of computational finance. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper investigates the pricing schemes of Cloud resources, which are distributed and parallel in nature. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may discuss the algorithms used for Cloud resource allocation and pricing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may discuss the software engineering aspects of developing market-driven mechanisms for Cloud spot pricing. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper may discuss the security and privacy concerns related to Cloud spot pricing.
